§ 6 Beſide theſe 3 ſignifications, in which the word in Greeke retained in our Language, is read in the old Teſtament, I am confident there is no other, ſave once Pſal. 50. 20, for ſlander, or calumny, or defamation, (for ſo the Hebrew there ſignifies) a ſenſe which is vulgar amongſt us in Engliſh;
